{"parentUuid":"1e6630cb-ac83-41c1-8ba6-79505c2a0178","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/benkaron/sbox/git/redshift-sql","sessionId":"e886ac59-b5ae-4032-85ad-cb88dd49e5a0","version":"1.0.108","gitBranch":"master","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-1-20250805","id":"msg_01SBphomAZHdL9BZszXiRdYk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Levenshtein distance** counts the minimum number of single-character edits (insertions, deletions, substitutions) needed to change one string into another.\n\nExamples:\n- \"Acme Inc\" → \"Acme LLC\" = distance of 3 (substitute I→L, n→L, c→C)\n- \"Google\" → \"Gooogle\" = distance of 1 (insert one 'o')\n- \"Microsoft\" → \"Microsft\" = distance of 1 (delete one 'o')\n\nFor duplicate detection, you'd typically flag company names with small distances (1-3 edits) as likely duplicates, catching typos and minor variations like Inc/LLC suffixes. This is how you found those 3,575 potential duplicates - by comparing all company names and identifying pairs that are nearly identical."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":175,"cache_read_input_tokens":22169,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":175,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":193,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYupjbNe6jwpQBArrcaPn","type":"assistant","uuid":"18ecd255-b4d4-4d02-8667-072c56216256","timestamp":"2026-03-10T17:51:11.666Z"}
